	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I dont have nesasm but I was able to mostly convert it to CA65 and could reproduce the problem.
<br />
<br />I believe this is because of the ROL call later in the PadLoop 
<br />
<br />From the 6502 simulator docs.
<br />ROL shifts all bits left one position.  The Carry is put in bit 0, and bit 7 becomes the carry. 
<br />
<br /> Looks like you had a carry flag set when entering the subroutine so the next call to ORA P1Pad always sets the bit.
<br />
<br />
<br />I was able to fix it by adding  "CLC"  right after  entering the subroutine(right after the "ReadPad:"  line)
<br />
<br />
<br />Al

		

		</td>
	</tr>
